Day 10: Stack – Valid Parentheses

Implement a stack to check if parentheses in a string are balanced.


Implement a min stack that supports push, pop, and min operations.


Implement next greater element using a stack.


Evaluate postfix expressions using a stack.


Sort a stack using recursion.


Day 11: Stack – Min Stack, NGE

Implement a min stack that returns the minimum element in constant time.


Find the next greater element for each element in an array.


Implement sort a stack using another stack.


Find the previous greater element for each element in an array.


Implement a dynamic stack that doubles its size when full.
